By clinging to consistency, you protect your porcelain identity,

35
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:07,620
the fragile, unchanging version of yourself that you spent years perfecting.

36
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:10,039
Keep a defensive archive, too.

37
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,919
Unsent letters, photos of your glory days,

38
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,379
a ledger of every wrong done to you.

39
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:18,240
These are your capital investments in misery.

40
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:22,800
The more you hoard them, the more you prove you were right all along.

41
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:27,219
And when change finally dares to knock, use the too-late fallacy.

42
